Browning-Ferris Industries Inc said theColorado Department of Health and the U.S. EnvironmentalProtection Agency have awarded the company permits to build andoperate a hazardous waste disposal site near Last Chance, Colo.    The company said construction will start this year and takeabout 12 months, costing about 14 to 16 mln dlrs.  It said ithas already spent 10 mln dlrs on development costs.    The site will not accept materials that react rapidly withair or water, explosives, shock sensitive materials orradioactive wastes, the company said. Reuter&#3;